<section id="To_control_the_power_state_of_one_Virtual_Machine" remap="TID_14856">
	<title>Controlling the Power State of Virtual Machines</title>
	<para>
		Start, stop, and suspend any number of virtual machines through the <productname>CloudForms Management Engine</productname> console using the following procedure.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Control the Power State of Virtual Machines</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu> <guisubmenu>Virtual Machines</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Check the virtual machines that you want to change the power state for.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1998.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Power Operations</guilabel>). Note that the only operations that will be available are the ones that apply to the virtual machines' current power state.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the button for the power operation you want.
			</para>
			<substeps>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/1999.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Power On</guilabel>) to start the selected virtual machines.
					</para>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2000.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Power Off</guilabel>) to stop the selected virtual machines.
					</para>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2004.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Suspend</guilabel>) to suspend the selected virtual machines.
					</para>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2001.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Reset</guilabel>) to stop the selected virtual machines.
					</para>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2002.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Shutdown Guest</guilabel>) to stop the guest operating system.
					</para>
				</step>
				<step>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2003.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Restart Guest</guilabel>) to restart the guest operating system.
					</para>
				</step>
			</substeps>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>OK</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>